  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN123.1-kilavi">
          <p type="edition"><app><lem wit="#NL #C5 #C9">talaimaka ṉiṭaiccurattut taṉṉeñciṟkuc colliyatu.</lem></app></p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What HE said to his own heart in the middle of the desert. (In this song, paṭivam [is] an observance).</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN123.1">
            <lg type="edition">
                <l>uṇṇā maiyi ṉuṟaṅkiya maruṅki</l>
                <l>ṉāṭāp paṭivat tāṉṟōr pōla</l>
                <l>varaiceṟi ciṟuneṟi niraiyuṭaṉ celluṅ</l>
                <l>kāṉa yāṉai kaviṉaḻi kuṉṟa</l>
                <l>miṟantuporu ṭarutalu māṟ<supplied>ṟāy</supplied> ciṟanta</l>
                <l>cillaiṅ kūnta ṉallakam porunti</l>
                <l>yoḻiyiṉ vaṟumai yañcuti yaḻitaka</l>
                <l>vuṭaiyai vāḻiya neñcē nilaveṉa</l>
                <l>neykaṉi neṭuvē leḵkilai yimaikku</l>
                <l>maḻaimaruḷ paḵṟōṉ māvaṇ cōḻar</l>
                <l>kaḻaimāy kāvirik kaṭaṉmaṇṭu peruntuṟai</l>
                <l>yiṟavoṭu vantu kōtaiyoṭu peyarum</l>
                <l>peruṅkaṭa lōtam pōla</l>
                <l>voṉṟiṟ koḷḷāy ceṉṟutaru poruṭkē.</l>
                
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l>You who cannot even bring wealth, traversing</l>
                <l>the hills where beauty has perished, with forest elephants</l>
                <l>that go together with the herd on the little path closed in by mountains,</l>
                <l>resembling noble men in the austerity of not bathing</l>
                <l>with [their] sides that are wearied because of not eating, (1-5)</l>
                <l>if you stayed behind,</l>
                <l>joined to the good bosom of [her with] excellent few tresses [styled in] five [ways]</l>
                <l rend="indent4">you would be afraid of poverty. You who are</l>
                <l>fit to perish, may you live, heart, (5d-8c)</l>
                <l>– because of the wealth to be brought by going, you who do not take up one thing,</l> 
                <l>resembling the flood of the great ocean</l>
                <l>that comes with prawn and goes back with garlands</l>
                <l>on the big ghat rushed at by the sea of the Kāviri where vanish bamboo [poles]</l>
                <l>of the great, generous Cōḻas with many cloud-like shields</l>
                <l>where the sharp tips of long spears on which oil has melted blink like moonlight. (8d-14)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
